We start with the “Fixed Assets” opening balance from the “Initial20231231001” row – which is 5,000,000.00.

Then we look for transactions that affect the asset account. In this ledger the only fixed asset “addition” is the “FixedAsset20231231001” row (type “Fixed Assets Purchase”) with an amount of 480,116.37. (The other purchase entries and expense items deal with operating costs and purchases of inventory or expenses). 

Depreciation is recorded as a separate entry so it is deducted from the gross fixed assets value. In our table there is one depreciation entry – “Depreciation20240101001” with an amount of 45,745.79.

Thus the ending net fixed assets are calculated as follows:

  Ending Fixed Assets = Opening Fixed Assets + Fixed Asset Purchase – Depreciation  
     = 5,000,000.00 + 480,116.37 – 45,745.79  
     = 5,480,116.37 – 45,745.79  
     = 5,434,370.58

Thus the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Fixed Assets Initial Value": "5000000.00",
    "Fixed Assets End Value": "5434370.58"
  }
}
